\series bold
th root of unity 
\series default
in a field is a solution to 
\begin_inset Formula $z^{n}=1$
\end_inset

, or equivalently is a root of 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{n}-1$
\end_inset

.
 There are at most 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 different 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

th roots of unity in a field since 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{n}-1$
\end_inset

 has at most 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 roots in any field.
 A 
\series bold
root of unity 
\series default
is an 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

th root of unity for some 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

.
 The only roots of unity in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 are 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm1$
\end_inset

, while in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

 there are 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 different 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

th roots of unity for each 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, namely 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta_{n}:=e^{2\pi ik/n}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq k\leq n-1$
\end_inset

 and they form a group of order 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

.
 In characteristic 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

