\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 to be the order of 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta$
\end_inset

 as a root of unity: the least exponent making 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta^{n}=1$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{n}-1$
\end_inset

 has every power of 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta$
\end_inset

 as a root, so it has 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 different roots: 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{n}-1$
\end_inset

 is 
\series bold
seperable 
\series default
over 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

.
 Conversely, if 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{n}-1$
\end_inset

 is separable over 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

, then it has 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 different roots, they are a group under multiplication, and 
